brainly_data.question: A farmer wishes to build a rectangular plot with 800 meters of wire fencing. use calculus to find the maximum area that can be enclosed by the fence
brainly_data.subject: Mathematics

all_answers.question: A farmer wishes to build a rectangular plot with 800 meters of wire fencing. use calculus to find the maximum area that can be enclosed by the fence
all_answers.subject: Mathematics
all_answers.text:
He has to build a square, so 800÷4=200
200²=40 000 m²
